column5: A nice little snack tonight  lake huron Smelt and fiddleheads from our 'backyard'    TB
all I got to say is....Yummy
That'll be adequate... for an "old" person that can't handle the "Big" fish eh!???

freekin awesome looking food. You see so many 'celebrity know it all chefs making money from preaching about fresh, local foods....like they friggin' invented it....lol (ooooops....was i ranting.......?)  top stuff Tinbanger  Bon appetite
Fiddleheads were close by but the smelt traveled about 600 km TB
All your missing is one of these    I picked my fiddle heads yesterday, but maybe we could work out a deal for some of those smelts  Sinker
